<div class="content"><nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › Pickup Truck Wraps</nav><h1>Pickup Truck Wraps Chicago</h1><p>Professional pickup truck wraps for contractors, service companies, and businesses across Chicago. Whether you need a full wrap, partial wrap, or simple lettering — we've wrapped <strong>thousands of pickup trucks</strong> over 24+ years.</p><h2>Trucks We Wrap</h2><ul><li><strong>Ford F-150, F-250, F-350</strong> — America's best-selling truck, templated for exact fit</li><li><strong>Chevrolet Silverado 1500/2500/3500</strong> — full and partial wrap options</li><li><strong>RAM 1500, 2500, 3500</strong> — including crew cab and extended bed</li><li><strong>Toyota Tundra and Tacoma</strong> — mid-size and full-size templates</li><li><strong>GMC Sierra</strong> — all cab configurations</li><li><strong>Nissan Titan and Frontier</strong> — work truck wrap packages</li></ul><h2>Wrap Options</h2><p><strong>Full wraps</strong> cover every painted surface for maximum impact — cab, bed, tailgate, bumpers, and mirrors. <strong>Partial wraps</strong> focus on high-visibility areas like doors, tailgate, and bed sides. <strong>Lettering packages</strong> add your logo, phone number, and website at the lowest cost.</p><h2>Pricing</h2><p>Pickup truck wrap pricing depends on cab size, bed length, and coverage level:</p><ul><li><strong>Full wrap</strong> — $3,500–$4,500 (regular cab to crew cab)</li><li><strong>Partial wrap</strong> — $1,500–$2,500</li><li><strong>Lettering package</strong> — $350–$800</li><li><strong>Tailgate only</strong> — $400–$700</li></ul><h2>Materials</h2><p>We use only premium <strong>cast vinyl</strong> from Avery Dennison (MPI 1105) and 3M (IJ180-CV3) — rated for 5–7 years of outdoor durability. Cast vinyl conforms to truck body lines, rivets, and corrugations without lifting.</p>
